article.headline: Valparaiso 76, Chicago St 69
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Ron Howard scored 21 points and grabbed eight rebounds, and Dan Oppland had 16 points as Valparaiso never relinquished its halftime lead to beat Chicago State 76-69 Monday night. The Crusaders (12-11, 8-3 Mid-Continent) led 33-27 at intermission after a half that saw 10 lead changes and survived a second half where the teams combined to score 85 points. Tony Weeden scored 21 points, Deji Akindele added 16 and grabbed seven rebounds, and Craig Franklin scored 10 points more to lead Chicago State (6-14, 5-5). Also scoring in double digits for Valparaiso were Seth Colclasure and Jimmie Myles, who had 10 points each.
